[src:scim-provisioning/provisioning-technology] On-demand self-service is described by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) as an essential characteristic of cloud computing.
[src:scim-provisioning/provisioning-technology] The self-service nature of cloud computing lets end users obtain and remove cloud services―including applications, the infrastructure supporting the applications, and configuration― themselves without requiring the assistance of an IT staff member.
